; Plaza Section — first vertical-slice walkable scene.
;
; This replaces the LS-002 stub (Node3D + Label3D) with a runnable demo of
; the foundation systems. Geometry is intentionally placeholder primitives
; (CSG nodes) — production assets land in a later content pass. The shape is
; a small enclosed 20m x 20m room with a few crates and a pillar so the
; player has something to walk around for the camera/movement demo.
;
; Conventions:
;   - Floor at world y=0; PlayerSpawn marker at y=1.0 so the capsule
;     (height=1.7) does not penetrate the floor on the first physics tick.
;   - Walls are 4 m tall, 0.5 m thick.
;   - Collision layer = 1 (LAYER_WORLD per ADR-0006 / PhysicsLayers).
;     PlayerCharacter masks WORLD, so collision works without further wiring.
;   - PlayerSpawn (Marker3D) is read by Main.gd at boot to position the
;     PlayerCharacter instance.
;
; Visual style alignment with the NOLF 1 brief lives in
; prototypes/visual_reference/ and will land in a later iteration of the
; outline pipeline + lighting pass — not in scope for this VS.

[sub_resource type="StandardMaterial3D" id="mat_floor"]
albedo_color = Color(0.58, 0.55, 0.50, 1.0)
roughness = 0.85

[sub_resource type="StandardMaterial3D" id="mat_wall"]
